description: A tool for managing symlinks.
sites_https_justification: The repository (due to being on GitHub) and documentation support HTTPS using TLS.

interact_justification: The README contains information about how to install emanate, open issues, and submit pull requests. <https://github.com/duckinator/emanate#readme>
contribution_justification: Projects on GitHub by default use issues and pull requests, as encouraged by documentation such as <https://guides.github.com/activities/contributing-to-open-source/>.
contribution_requirements_justification: The requirements are just "follow the existing code style." In practice, this has never presented a problem in the 3 years Emanate has existed.
license_location_justification: Non-trivial license location file in repository: <https://github.com/duckinator/emanate/blob/master/LICENSE.txt>.
floss_license_justification: The MIT license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
floss_license_osi_justification: The MIT license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
documentation_basics_justification: Documentation is at <https://emanate.smallest.dog/>, which is linked to from the GitHub repository.
documentation_interface_justification: Documentation of the interfaces is available at <https://emanate.smallest.dog/>, with the command-line interface documented at <https://emanate.smallest.dog/cli.html>.
repo_public_justification: Repository on GitHub, which provides public git repositories with URLs.
repo_track_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git can track the changes, who made them, and when they were made.
repo_interim_justification: The master branch contains all of the latest changes, without exception. Releases are split directly off of master. All changes are made through pull requests, including those by project maintainers.
repo_distributed_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git is distributed.
version_unique_justification: Emanate is released on PyPi, which inherently requires this.
release_notes_justification: Release notes for each release will be available under GitHub Releases starting with the version after v7.0.0: https://github.com/duckinator/emanate/releases
report_tracker_justification: GitHub is used for the issue tracker. <https://github.com/duckinator/emanate/issues>
report_process_justification: GitHub is used for users to submit bug reports. <https://github.com/duckinator/emanate/issues>
report_responses_justification: All issues so far have been acknowledged in 2-3 days. Most were fully resolved in less than a week.
enhancement_responses_justification: Most enhancement requests are responded to within 48 hours.
vulnerability_report_process_justificati: The README says to report security issues as normal. https://github.com/duckinator/emanate/blob/master/README.md
vulnerability_report_private_justificati: Security issues are not reported privately.
vulnerability_report_response_justificat: There have been no vulnerability reports.
build_justification: Install bork via pip, then run `bork build`.
build_common_tools_justification: Bork is not a common build tool, but it is available via pip.
build_floss_tools_justification: Python + Bork + setuptools are open source.
test_justification:
The test suite is in the GitHub repository: <https://github.com/duckinator/emanate/tree/master/tests>.
The build history is publicly available: <https://cirrus-ci.com/github/duckinator/emanate>
test_invocation_justification: The test suite uses Pytest, and can be invoked via either Pytest directly or via Bork.
test_most_justification: We have an open issue about getting code coverage information: https://github.com/duckinator/emanate/issues/251
tests_documented_added_justification: The policy on adding tests is mentioned in the README: https://github.com/duckinator/emanate/blob/master/README.md
warnings_justification: `bork run lint` runs a linter, and CI runs this.
warnings_fixed_justification: There are currently no warnings, and adding any results in a test failure.
warnings_strict_justification: There are currently no warnings, and adding any results in a test failure.
delivery_mitm_justification: All distribution methods are via HTTPS.
static_analysis_often_justification: Pylint is included in continuous integration, on every commit.
test_continuous_integration_justificatio: Cirrus CI (<https://cirrus-ci.com/github/duckinator/emanate>) is used for continuous integration, and bors (<https://bors.tech>) is used to avoid semantic conflicts.
discussion_justification: GitHub supports discussions on issues and pull requests.
english_justification: The primary developer only speaks English, so this happened by default.

repo_public_justification: Repository on GitHub, which provides public git repositories with URLs.
repo_track_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git can track the changes, who made them, and when they were made.
repo_interim_justification:

The main README shows the latest stable and alpha version.
repo_distributed_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git is distributed.
version_unique_justification: We use the software semantic versining 2.0 format: https://semver.org/
version_tags_justification: We do releases from GitHub so they are automatically tagged in git.
release_notes_justification: Release notes with each release in the Releases of GitHub: https://github.com/SceneGate/Yarhl/releases
release_notes_vulns_justification: There have been no publicly known vulnerabilities.
report_tracker_justification: GitHub provides an issue tracker: https://github.com/SceneGate/Yarhl/issues
report_process_justification:
GitHub provides an issue tracker. We provide templates for the issue reporting: https://github.com/SceneGate/Yarhl/blob/master/.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/bug_report.md
Also explained in the contributing document: https://github.com/SceneGate/Yarhl/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#reporting-issues
report_responses_justification:
We review new submitted issues and applied a label as soon as possible. Bugs are tipically addressed in the next release.
https://github.com/SceneGate/Yarhl/issues?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+label%3Abug
enhancement_responses_justification:
Every enhancement is reviewed, labels applied and most of them commented: https://github.com/SceneGate/Yarhl/issues?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+label%3Aenhancement
Some of them even marked to be addressed in the next release
report_archive_justification: GitHub issues are never deleted can be always searched: https://github.com/SceneGate/Yarhl/issues
vulnerability_report_process_justificati: The process is explained in SECURITY.md: https://github.com/SceneGate/Yarhl/blob/master/SECURITY.md
vulnerability_report_private_justificati: Vulnerabilities are submitted privately to an email address. GitHub provides features for private collaboration on the fix. https://github.com/SceneGate/Yarhl/blob/master/SECURITY.md
vulnerability_report_response_justificat: No known vulnerability has been reported.
build_justification: The project provides a build system in Cake that can be run locally and it's run by the CI: https://github.com/SceneGate/Yarhl/blob/master/build.cake
build_common_tools_justification: We use the standard tool for C# projects: Cake https://cakebuild.net/
test_justification: The project has a project with all the unit tests: https://github.com/SceneGate/Yarhl/tree/master/src/Yarhl.UnitTests
test_invocation_justification: The unit tests are written in NUnit so there is integration with all the C# IDE. As well it can be run with "dotnet test".
test_most_justification:
There is 100% of code coverage https://sonarcloud.io/component_measures?id=yarhl&metric=coverage&view=list
The CI will fail if this is not the case.
test_policy_justification:
The CI and build scripts will fail if the test coverage is not 100%. We aim to test every new functionality.
This is also explained in the contributing document: https://github.com/SceneGate/Yarhl/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#quality
tests_are_added_justification: The CI and build scripts will fail if the test coverage is not 100%.
tests_documented_added_justification: It is explained in the contributing document: https://github.com/SceneGate/Yarhl/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#quality
warnings_justification:
The CI and build system ensures the code quality with the following checks:
* Compiler warnings
* Gendarme linter (FLOSS)
* SonarCube linter
warnings_fixed_justification: No warning is present and the CI will fail if so.
warnings_strict_justification: No warning is allowed and the CI will fail if so.
delivery_mitm_justification: The library doesn't retrieve HTTP URLs.
delivery_unsigned_justification: The library doesn't retrieve HTTP URLs.
vulnerabilities_fixed_60_days_justificat: No public known vulnerability reported and enabled GitHub alerts for security issues.
vulnerabilities_critical_fixed_justifica: No public known vulnerability reported and enabled GitHub alerts for security issues.
static_analysis_justification:
Gendarme (FLOSS)
Several Roslyn extra linters
Sonar
LGTM
static_analysis_fixed_justification: Everything reported by linters is fixed to make the PR and CI pass.
static_analysis_often_justification: Static source code analysis happens always on every push, PR and build.
dynamic_analysis_justification: Every release as well as PR must pass all the quality checks
test_continuous_integration_justificatio: There is CI with Azure DevOps: https://dev.azure.com/SceneGate/Yarhl/_build?definitionId=1
discussion_justification: GitHub supports discussions on issues and pull requests.
no_leaked_credentials_justification: No key is provided and when necessary they are encrypted in the CI servers.
english_justification: Code, documentation and issues is provided in English.
